      "action": "Emergency lockdown of the Seal Verification Chamber's consecrated archive, revoking the Lacquer Authority's supervised access and deploying shrine auditors to conduct a full inventory audit of all seal templates and consecrated matrices. The Council also initiates liturgical re-consecration protocols to invalidate any copied templates, rendering the Authority's stolen catalog useless.",
      "outcome": "The lockdown catches the Lacquer Authority's artificers mid-operation — several are discovered attempting to make unauthorized rubbings of high-value seal matrices and are detained by shrine auditors. The Council's audit reveals that while the Authority successfully cataloged the archive's contents, the re-consecration protocols scramble the liturgical encryption keys on all primary templates, making the copied catalog obsolete. The Authority's foothold in the archive is severed, but the diplomatic fallout is severe — the Authority publicly denounces the Council as \"bureaucratic tyrants\" and accelerates negotiations with the Guild Wardens. The Signal-House Families, caught between their alliance with the Council and their licensing treaty with the Authority, send envoys to mediate. The Council's archive is secure, but they have made a powerful enemy.",
      "targetLocation": "Seal Verification Chamber",
      "tagChangeCount": 2,
      "chronicleEntryId": "e2633df6-f14d-4e23-a196-e0fe15487359"
