      "action": "Deploy shrine auditors to conduct public liturgical audits of Canal Market District merchants, offering free \"spiritual verification\" of their cargo manifests and transit documents. The audits serve dual purposes: demonstrating the Council's benevolent spiritual authority to counter Warden corruption narratives, and quietly identifying which merchants have been spreading Warden-aligned counter-narratives. Simultaneously, the Council's secretive inner circle revokes the Lacquer Authority's supervised archive access, citing \"procedural irregularities\" discovered during a routine audit of access logs, and stations additional cryptographic wardens to guard the Seal Verification Chamber's consecrated seal matrices.",
      "outcome": "The public audits are well-received by smaller merchants who cannot afford the Signal-House Families' premium service but distrust the Wardens' extortionate tariffs. Several merchants who had been spreading Warden counter-narratives are identified and quietly blacklisted from consecrated signal routes. The revocation of Lacquer Authority access catches the Authority's agents mid-catalog — they are expelled before completing their inventory, though several seal templates have already been copied. The Authority protests the revocation, but the Council cites binding liturgical protocols that override commercial agreements. The Seal Verification Chamber is now under heightened security, with access restricted to Council-loyal auditors only. The Wardens' counter-narrative loses momentum as merchants witness the Council's visible, helpful presence in the market district.",
      "targetLocation": "Canal Market District",
      "tagChangeCount": 3,
      "chronicleEntryId": "0670f668-7a6a-44c1-924f-a36333c29c13"
    }
