      "outcome": "The acoustic dead-zone is successfully established — any monitoring equipment brought within three stone-throws of the Vault now registers only white noise and phantom harmonics. The silence-locks engage with a deep, subsonic thrum that reverberates through the Spire's foundations, felt but not heard by outsiders. The Shrine Auditors' Council, who had been quietly surveying the Spire's exterior for potential consecration points, finds their instruments rendered useless. The Signal-House Families' agents, scouting the Spire for potential \"authenticated relay\" installations, report back that the structure appears dormant and inert — exactly as the Keepers intend. The cipher scripture project continues undisturbed, protected by layers of acoustic obfuscation that grow more sophisticated with each passing day. The Keepers have turned the Spire into a black box: visible to all, legible to none.",
