    [35mpayload[39m: {
      "action": "With the Guild Wardens' garrison withdrawn from the canal approach, the Signal-House Families move swiftly to consolidate control over the Lantern-Lit Gondola Pier. They recruit additional gondola operators into their subsidized freight network, offering favorable rates to any vessel willing to carry Signal-House routing ciphers. Simultaneously, they dispatch their most trusted cryptographers to begin reconnaissance of the Night Courier Depot — mapping its layout, identifying key personnel, and locating the routing ledger that controls message distribution across the Canal Market District. The Families establish a covert observation post in a warehouse overlooking the Depot's main entrance, documenting guard rotations and ledger access protocols.",
      "outcome": "The Signal-House Families' subsidized freight network expands significantly as operators, emboldened by the Wardens' retreat and the consecrated charter, flock to the pier. Within days, the Families' message-courier gondolas outnumber the Wardens' permitted vessels three-to-one on key canal routes. The reconnaissance of the Night Courier Depot reveals that the routing ledger is kept in a locked administrative office accessible only to the Depot's Master of Routes — a bureaucratic official who answers to no single faction but is known to be susceptible to financial inducement. The Families' agents identify a potential intermediary: a retired signal operator named Vellaro who once served the Depot and still maintains personal connections to its staff. The Families' commercial dominance at the pier is now undeniable, and the first phase of their campaign to seize the routing ledger has begun.",
      "targetLocation": "Lantern-Lit Gondola Pier",
